-- CTC Media Loses Audience Share; Drops to Sixth Most-Watched
-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 2012-05-03T15:32:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-03/ctc-media-loses-audience-share-drops-to-sixth-most-watched.html
CTC Media Inc. (CTCM) ’s average daily share
of viewers 18 years and older for its television channel fell to
5.5 percent in the week to April 29, pushing it one level down
to the sixth-most watched in Russia, according to TNS-Global.  Viewer share for CTC TV, the Nasdaq-listed Russian media
company’s biggest source of revenue, dropped from 5.9 percent in
the previous week, data researcher TNS-Global said by e-mail
today. CTC’s average daily audience among viewers 4 years old
and over declined to 6.5 percent in the week to April 29 from
6.8 percent in the week to April 22, the data show.  CTC lost its fifth-place ranking among viewers 18 years and
older it had regained in the week to April 22.  Russia ’s  NTV
Television , the government-controlled  Pervyi Kanal , Rossiya-1,
TNT and Piatyi Kanal were all ahead of CTC among viewers 18 and
over. CTC retained its fifth place among viewers 4 years old and
over, TNS-Global said.  NTV maintained its top ranking in both categories, with its
share of viewers 18 years and over rising to 16.1 percent in the
week to April 29, compared with a 14.8 percent share in the
previous week, according to TNS-Global. Pervyi’s share of
viewers 18 years and over was unchanged at 14.7 percent.  Rossiya-1’s share of the average daily audience 18 years
and over was 12.5 percent in the week, compared with 13.1
percent in the previous week, TNS-Global said. TNT had an 8.1
percent share, up from 7.6 percent. Piatyi Kanal’s share was at
5.6 percent.  CTC Media also owns some smaller television channels in
Russia, including Domashniy and Peretz.  To contact the reporters on this story:
